dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset of 5,000 Stochastic-Block-Model graphs with 30 nodes divided into 3 different communities. The probabilities of generating edges connecting nodes within the same community are [0.2, 0.3, 0.4], while the probability of generating edges between nodes of different communities is 0.1.
dcterms:title: Stochastic-Block-Model graphs

dcterms:description: A dataset of Erdos-Renyi graphs with 10 nodes and edge generation probabilities of 0.3 for the first dataset and 0.8 for the out-of-distribution dataset.
dcterms:title: Erdos-Renyi graphs

dcterms:creator: H. Maron
B. Ben-Hamu
H. Serviansky
Y. Lipman
dcterms:description: PPGN is a graph neural network architecture that represents the graph structure in a tensor and exploits tensor multiplications to enhance expressivity, capable of counting patterns of size three.
dcterms:title: PPGN

dcterms:creator: Y. Huang
X. Peng
J. Ma
M. Zhang
dcterms:description: I2-GNN is a graph neural network architecture designed to decompose the whole graph into different subgraphs and process them independently, developed to count arbitrary patterns of size four.
dcterms:title: I2-GNN
